    <etym xml:lang="ru">Тюркское слово, широко распространенное в кавказских языках: <mentioned
            xml:lang="trk"><lang/><w>čojun</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="trk"
            ><w>čuhun</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w>čüjün</w></mentioned>, ,
            <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>čudan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xmf"
                ><lang/><w>čuvani</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="xmf"
        ><w>čivani</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="lzz"
            ><lang/><w>čuveni</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="lzz"><w>čoǧeni</w></mentioned>, ,
            <mentioned xml:lang="ka-x-dial"><lang/><w>čoina</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">
                        (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Беридзе"/></bibl>)</note><note type="comment"
                xml:lang="en"> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Беридзе"/></bibl>)</note></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="sva"><lang/><w>čweni</w><gloss><q>котел</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/><w>čojen</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/><w>čuon</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"
                ><w>čon</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><w>čuina</w></mentioned>, ,
            <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/><w>šuan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="uby"
                ><lang/><w>čuwan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ab"
            ><lang/><w>čwan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="abq"
            ><lang/><w>čuan</w></mentioned>.<mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>чугун</w></mentioned>
        относится сюда же. В дигорском диалекте сохранилась форма, более близкая к русской:
            <mentioned xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/><w>cigon</w><gloss><q>чугунный
                котелок</q></gloss></mentioned>. Значения ‘чугун’ и ‘котел’ повсюду
        переплетаются.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">A turkic word widespread in Caucasian languages: <mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                ><lang/><w>čojun</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w>čuhun</w></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w>čüjün</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>čudan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xmf"
            ><lang/><w>čuvani</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="xmf"><w>čivani</w></mentioned>, ,
            <mentioned xml:lang="lzz"><lang/><w>čuveni</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="lzz"
                ><w>čoǧeni</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ka-x-dial"
                ><lang/><w>čoina</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (<bibl><ref
                        target="#ref_Беридзе"/></bibl>)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                        (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Беридзе"/></bibl>)</note></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sva"><lang/><w>čweni</w><gloss><q>kettle</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="av"><lang/><w>čojen</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"
                ><lang/><w>čuon</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"
            ><w>čon</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><w>čuina</w></mentioned>, ,
            <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/><w>šuan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="uby"
                ><lang/><w>čuwan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ab"
            ><lang/><w>čwan</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="abq"
            ><lang/><w>čuan</w></mentioned>.<mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>čugun</w></mentioned>
        refers here. In Digor there is a form which more close to the Russian one: <mentioned
            xml:lang="os-x-digor"><lang/><w>cigon</w><gloss><q>cast iron little
            kettle</q></gloss></mentioned>. Meanings ‘cast iron’ and ‘kettle’ interwine
        everywhere.</etym>
